Class BasePermissionValidator

    public abstract class BasePermissionValidator
extends java.lang.Object
implements PermissionValidator
    Base class containing help method for performing permission validation of Ieee1609 and ETSI 103097 certificates.

      • checkAppPermissions

        protected void checkAppPermissions(EndEntityType endEntityType,
                                   int chainLength,
                                   Certificate certificate,
                                   Certificate issuer)
                            throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException,
                                   InvalidCertificateException
        Help method to check app permission of an certificate against permissions in its issuer. If certificate contains certRequestPermissions is InvalidCertificateException thrown since it is not supported in ETSI 103097 PKIs.
        Parameters:
        endEntityType - the end entity type to evaluate permissions for.
        chainLength - the current index in the chain evaulation, starts at 0 and is incremented.
        certificate - the certificate to check permissions for towards it issuer
        issuer - the issuer certificate.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if one of the parameter contained invalid data.
        InvalidCertificateException - if certificate contained invalid permissions.

      • hasAllPermissions

        protected boolean hasAllPermissions(EndEntityType endEntityType,
                                    int chainLength,
                                    SequenceOfPsidGroupPermissions sequenceOfPsidGroupPermissions)
                             throws InvalidCertificateException
        Method that check if a certificate has all permissions and if so returns true, unless there is more than one all permission, then is InvalidCertificateException thrown.
        Parameters:
        endEntityType - the target end entity type of permissions to lookup.
        chainLength - the cirrent chain length to look up permissions for, 0 for end entity 1 for it's issuer and up.
        sequenceOfPsidGroupPermissions - a sequence of PsidGroupPermissions to check if all permissions exists.
        Returns:
        true if certificate have one all permissions.
        Throws:
        InvalidCertificateException - if more than one all permissions exists.

      • filterPsidSspRangeByPSID

        protected java.util.List<PsidSspRange> filterPsidSspRangeByPSID(long psid,
                                                                java.util.List<PsidGroupPermissions> psidGroupPermissions)
                                                         throws InvalidCertificateException
        Method to filter out all PsidSppRange for a specific psid, it traverses through all PsidGroupPermissions in the list and only selects items.
        Parameters:
        psid - the psid to filter by.
        psidGroupPermissions - List of psidGroupPermsissions that have been filtered by filterByEndEntityTypeAndChainLength before this call.
        Returns:
        List of PsidSspRange with specified psid
        Throws:
        InvalidCertificateException - if subjectPermissions contains sequence of SequenceOfPsidSspRange not containing PsidSspRange objects.

      • filterPsidSspByPSID

        protected java.util.List<PsidSsp> filterPsidSspByPSID(long psid,
                                                      SequenceOfPsidSsp sequenceOfPsidSsp)
                                               throws InvalidCertificateException
        Method that filters out a sequence of PsidSsp and returns a list of PsidSsp with matching PSID only.
        Parameters:
        psid - the psid to filter.
        sequenceOfPsidSsp - sequence of PsidSsp to filter.
        Returns:
        a list of matching PsidSsp, never null.
        Throws:
        InvalidCertificateException - if encoding of certificate was invalid, i.e SequenceOfPsidSsp didn't contain PsidSsp.

      • filterByEndEntityTypeAndChainLength

        protected java.util.List<PsidGroupPermissions> filterByEndEntityTypeAndChainLength(EndEntityType endEntityType,
                                                                                   int chainLength,
                                                                                   COEREncodable[] psidGroupPermissions)
                                                                            throws InvalidCertificateException
        Method that filter out PsidGroupPermissions that have a specified end entity type and within the chain length specified.
        Parameters:
        endEntityType - the end entity type (i.e. app or enrol) that should be matched.
        chainLength - the chain length that should be within minChainDepth and minChainDepth + chainDepthRange.
        psidGroupPermissions - the array of psidGroupPermissions from certificate.
        Returns:
        a list of matching PsidGroupPermissions never null
        Throws:
        InvalidCertificateException - if encoding of certificate was invalid, i.e array of psidGroupPermissions didn't contain PsidGroupPermissions.
